c.2016.03.003">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27473801/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Laparoscopic+Roux-en-Y+gastric+bypass%3A+surgical+technique+and+perioperative+care&amp;author=L+Berbiglia&amp;author=JG+Zografakis&amp;author=AG+Dan&amp;publication_year=2016&amp;journal=Surg+Clin+North+Am&amp;pages=773-794&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.suc.2016.03.003&amp;pmid=27473801">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">11.</div><div id="r11" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Kawkabani Marchini A, Denys A, Paroz A, et al. The four different types of internal hernia occurring after laparascopic Roux-en-Y gastric bypass performed for morbid obesity: are there any multidetector computed tomography (MDCT) features permitting their distinction? <em>Obes Surg</em> 2011;21(4):506–516.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11695-011-0364-7">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21318275/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=The+four+different+types+of+internal+hernia+occurring+after+laparascopic+Roux-en-Y+gastric+bypass+performed+for+morbid+obesity%3A+are+there+any+multidetector+computed+tomography+%28MDCT%29+features+permitting+their+distinction%3F&amp;author=A+Kawkabani+Marchini&amp;author=A+Denys&amp;author=A+Paroz&amp;publication_year=2011&amp;journal=Obes+Surg&amp;pages=506-516&amp;doi=10.1007%2Fs11695-011-0364-7&amp;pmid=21318275">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">12.</div><div id="r12" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Hope WW, Sing RF, Chen AY, et al. Fai